Description: Acumence is a business intelligence platform that enables companies to monitor and analyze.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Acumence is a business intelligence platform that enables companies to monitor and analyze manufacturing operations in order to measure and improve performance. The company’s Manufacturing Business Intelligence Solution provides real-time views and historical metrics about what is actually happening on the factory floor and helps companies leverage their capital expenditures in equipment and ERP systems. Real-time and transactional production data are organized so that enterprise manufacturing BI can be delivered to all the people who need it, when, and how they need it most. Its Operational Efficiency Gap Analysis solution offers insight into actual efficiency losses, and identifies gaps in performance that can be improved at the operational level. So it will identify concrete opportunities for improvement, as well as benefits and ROI analysis for finance.  Since its inception, Acumence has run manufacturing lines, engineered and built manufacturing processes, planned and project managed the electrical engineering requirements for numerous high-speed manufacturers, architected and installed electrical control systems for entire factories, designed and built custom OEM manufacturing machinery, and developed mission critical manufacturing production process methodologies from control systems to management standards.  Their client portfolio includes Motorola, Kraft, EcoLab, Nalco, Rexam, Clorox, USG, and Stepan with projects throughout North America, South America, Europe, and China. In addition, the company conducts audits of existing plants, highlighting inefficiencies, and offering opportunities for improvement, both by lowering costs and increasing revenues. Furthermore, it offers discrete part manufacturers with a solution that could be supported locally at the plant level or centrally at the corporate level without the need for any special programming language skills. Acumence was founded by Chris Chandler and Joe Jablonski in January 1997 and is based in Chicago, Illinois, the United States.

Full Description: JustFundraising.com has helped over 34,500 groups raise a combined $81 million, so far. Over the past 12 years, we’ve been earning the trust and respect of groups coast-to-coast by offering quality fundraising programs, exceptional customer service, and our price-match promise. We’re fanatical about fundraising and we genuinely care about your success which is reflected in our 98.7% rate of customer satisfaction. We’re committed to helping your group raise more! Quality Fundraising Products: Your group wants to sell products they’re proud of. Your supporters want value, and we give it to them! Many of your supporters are family, friends and neighbors – it’s only fair they receive the value you would expect. As well, satisfied supporters will order more product in future fundraisers if they’re satisfied with their initial purchase, which is crucial for repeat business. Our team carefully scouts and selects our quality fundraising products at the industry trade shows, which we attend a few times annually. The Right Fundraisers: Your group is unique, so your choice of fundraising products needs to be carefully considered. Amongst other criteria, we consider age, local demographics, past fundraising successes, your local fundraising competition, and your group’s personal preferences. We’ve expanded our fundraising product line to include frozen and non-frozen food products, healthier fundraisers, green fundraisers, massive holiday shoppers. Our price points vary from as low as $0.50, all the way up to $30. We offer in-hand direct-sellers, as well as order-takers. We’ve got the right fundraiser for you! Highest Profit Backed by Our Price-Match Promise: Your goal is to raise as much profit as possible, and we’re committed to helping you do exactly that. If you find a better price or percentage profit with another company, simply fax or email us the details, and we’ll match it, and send you a free tub of cookie dough. This guarantee is good for 30 days after your invoice is paid. Free, Free, Free: All of our order-taker fundraisers are no money up-front fundraisers (order-takers landing page), meaning they are free to start. You receive free shipping on ALL direct-seller products. You receive free shipping on all order-taker fundraisers when you reach a very achievable minimum sales target. This means more profit in your pocket. Superior Support: We do our best to equip you with the best online and offline support in order to optimize your time and help your group raise more. Firstly, you’ll be designated your own personal fundraising assistant to help you select, plan out, and support your fundraiser from beginning to end. All emails and phone calls are promptly returned within 1 hour, during regular business hours. Secondly, the selling material for all order-takers is second-to-none and virtually does all the selling for you. Thirdly, you can now access our new online Create Your Group Fundraising Page (page not created yet). This new tool will allow you to keep in constant touch with your fundraising participants and their parents, communicate who the best sellers are at any moment, and allow you and your participants to promote your fundraiser to your social network, again helping your group raise more. Finally, we really do care about your goals and we’re anxious to add you to our growing list of success stories.
